# TEST CASES FOLDER STRUCTURE

## Layout: `Cursor-Project/test_cases/`

Two sibling folders at top level:

| Folder | Meaning | When to use |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| **Objects/** | Tests grouped by entity | Product_contract, Service_contract, Customer, Invoice, POD |
| **Flows/** | Tests grouped by business flow | Contract_termination, Billing, Payment, Registration |

### Objects: `test_cases/Objects/<Entity_name>/<action>.md`
Example: `test_cases/Objects/Product_contract/Create.md`

### Flows: `test_cases/Flows/<Flow_name>/<scenario>.md`
Example: `test_cases/Flows/Contract_termination/Multi_version_termination_date.md`

### README in each folder
When adding a new entity or flow folder, update the corresponding README.

### Content
Each `.md` MUST follow **`Cursor-Project/config/Test_case_template.md`**: title, Jira, Type, Summary, Scope, Test data, then TC-1/TC-2/... with Objective, Preconditions, Steps, Expected result, Actual result (if bug), References. Include both **(Positive)** and **(Negative)** test cases. Write in detailed, human-readable English.
